</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="8" pageNumber="281" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="8.[151,1437,1315,2024]" pageId="8" pageNumber="281">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,1819,1844]" pageId="8" pageNumber="281">Remarks.</emphasis>
The closest species to 
<taxonomicName box="[578,751,1819,1844]" class="Demospongiae" family="Raspailiidae" genus="Eurypon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Poecilosclerida" pageId="8" pageNumber="281" phylum="Porifera" rank="species" species="distyli" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[578,751,1819,1844]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="281">Eurypon distyli</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[760,851,1819,1844]" pageId="8" pageNumber="281">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[760,851,1819,1844]" pageId="8" pageNumber="281" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
is 
<taxonomicName box="[886,1021,1819,1844]" class="Demospongiae" family="Raspailiidae" genus="Eurypon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Poecilosclerida" pageId="8" pageNumber="281" phylum="Porifera" rank="species" species="radiatum">
<emphasis box="[886,1021,1819,1844]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="281">E. radiatum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from the Azores because both share the posession of two categories of subectosomal styles and one category of acanthostyle, although 
<taxonomicName box="[1299,1436,1855,1880]" class="Demospongiae" family="Raspailiidae" genus="Eurypon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Poecilosclerida" pageId="8" pageNumber="281" phylum="Porifera" rank="species" species="radiatum">
<emphasis box="[1299,1436,1855,1880]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="281">E. radiatum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
lacks choanosomal subtylostyles and raphides. Aside from these two species no other 
<taxonomicName box="[1121,1217,1893,1916]" class="Demospongiae" family="Raspailiidae" genus="Eurypon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Poecilosclerida" pageId="8" pageNumber="281" phylum="Porifera" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1121,1217,1893,1916]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="281">Eurypon</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
described from the Atlantic have two categories of subectosomal styles. Other species from Atlantic that resemble 
<taxonomicName box="[1223,1395,1927,1952]" class="Demospongiae" family="Raspailiidae" genus="Eurypon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Poecilosclerida" pageId="8" pageNumber="281" phylum="Porifera" rank="species" species="distyli" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[1223,1395,1927,1952]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="281">Eurypon distyli</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="281">
<taxonomicNameLabel pageId="8" pageNumber="281" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
is 
<taxonomicName box="[233,330,1963,1988]" class="Demospongiae" family="Raspailiidae" genus="Eurypon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Poecilosclerida" pageId="8" pageNumber="281" phylum="Porifera" rank="species" species="viride">
<emphasis box="[233,330,1963,1988]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="281">E. viride</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, both having raphides. However, 
<taxonomicName box="[709,806,1963,1988]" class="Demospongiae" family="Raspailiidae" genus="Eurypon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Poecilosclerida" pageId="8" pageNumber="281" phylum="Porifera" rank="species" species="viride">
<emphasis box="[709,806,1963,1988]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="281">E. viride</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has small raphides (
<number box="[1036,1065,1964,1988]" pageId="8" pageNumber="281" value="70.0">70</number>
µm long), tylostyles and a white color compared to large raphides (
<number box="[534,577,2000,2024]" pageId="8" pageNumber="281" value="280.0">280</number>
µm long), subtylostyles and a green color in 
<taxonomicName box="[1084,1184,1999,2024]" class="Demospongiae" family="Raspailiidae" genus="Eurypon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Poecilosclerida" pageId="8" pageNumber="281" phylum="Porifera" rank="species" species="distyli" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[1084,1184,1999,2024]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="281">E. distyli</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1191,1281,1999,2024]" pageId="8" pageNumber="281">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1191,1281,1999,2024]" pageId="8" pageNumber="281" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
(Table 
<number box="[1366,1379,2000,2024]" pageId="8" pageNumber="281" value="1.0">1</number>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
